<P>
<S ID='S-119' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> Suppose that , in addition to the tree shown in Figure <CREF/> the grammar generates the pair of trees shown in Figure <CREF/> . </S>
<S ID='S-120' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> Notice that while the feature structures at the root of <EQN/> and <EQN/> are not compatible with <EQN/> and <EQN/> , they do agree with respect to those parts that are fully expanded at <EQN/> 's root node . </S>
<S ID='S-121' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> The `` context-freeness '' of PLPATR means that given the three trees shown in Figures <CREF/> and <CREF/> the tree shown in Figure <CREF/> will also be generated by the grammar . </S>
